_:N15cdbd687635468f9d43fc610d6dedcd <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>There are several different ways you can work for the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr>: <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-nsc-code-of-practice/uk-nsc-code-of-practice#appointing-new-uk-nsc-members\">become a member of the committee</a>, join one of the committee’s <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-national-screening-committee/about/our-governance#expert-and-advisory-groups\">expert reference groups</a> that advise on specific areas, or work for the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"become-a-member-of-the-committee\">Become a member of the committee</h2>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>The committee currently has no vacancies.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-national-screening-committee/about/our-governance#uk-national-screening-committee-uk-nsc\">committee membership</a> normally includes individuals from public life, academia and practising clinicians who have expertise in one or more relevant areas. Members of the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> are appointed for a fixed term as individuals and not as representatives of any organisations, after which time the role is open to new applicants, who can apply through the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/\">Civil Service Jobs</a> website.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"become-a-member-of-a-uk-nsc-expert-reference-group\">Become a member of a <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> expert reference group</h2>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>The <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> expert reference groups currently have no vacancies.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3 id=\"applying-for-reference-group-vacancies\">Applying for reference group vacancies</h3>\n\n<p>To apply for a reference group vacancy (when advertised), you should submit an expression of interest and a biography (up to 500 words or an A4 page) detailing your relevant experience and engagement with screening and how you can contribute to the workings of the reference group.  </p>\n\n<p>Email your application form or any enquiries to <a href=\"mailto:uknsc@dhsc.gov.uk\">uknsc@dhsc.gov.uk</a>. Please use the reference group name and post title in your email subject line.</p>\n\n<p>If you do not receive an acknowledgement of your application within 5 working days, please get in touch.  </p>\n\n<p>Applications will be reviewed by a panel of the reference group, including the chair and 2 members of the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat team. </p>\n\n<p>We will assess the application forms against the skills and experience outlined above and make our selection on that basis. Shortlisted applicants will be invited to a telephone interview.  </p>\n\n<p>All applications will receive a successful or unsuccessful notification. The successful candidates will receive information about next steps.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"work-for-the-uk-nscs-secretariat\">Work for the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr>’s secretariat</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat is based in the Department of Health and Social Care and provides specialist and administrative support to the committee.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>The <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat currently has no vacancies. Vacancies are advertised through the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/\">Civil Service Jobs</a> website.</p>\n</div>\n\n</div>" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
